 "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints"}, {"id": 171502053, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxNzE1MDIwNTM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-borrow-checker", "name": "A-borrow-checker", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: The borrow checker"}, {"id": 211668100, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgxMDA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-compiler", "name": "T-compiler", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2021-04-17T17:13:34Z", "updated_at": "2023-04-05T17:29:32Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nstruct Foo<'a> {\r\n    val: &'a mut bool\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn consume(_foo: Foo<'_>, _val: bool) {}\r\n\r\nfn bar(val: &mut bool) {\r\n    let foo = Foo { val };\r\n    consume(foo, *val);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nproduces the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror[E0503]: cannot use `*val` because it was mutably borrowed\r\n --> src/lib.rs:9:18\r\n  |\r\n8 |     let foo = Foo { val };\r\n  |                     --- borrow of `*val` occurs here\r\n9 |     consume(foo, *val);\r\n  |     -------      ^^^^ use of borrowed `*val`\r\n  |     |\r\n  |     borrow later used by call\r\n\r\nerror: aborting due to previous error\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error message points at the uses of `val`, and the call to `consume`. However, the error message does not indicate that the usage of `foo` in the argument to `consume` is also at fault.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84273/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api